    <title>Combined summary - Backward deterministic R Value</title>
    <updated>2023-06-02T00:26:17.690660+00:00</updated>
    <link href="https://lists.linuxfoundation.org/pipermail/lightning-dev/2016-March/000477.html" rel="alternate"/>
    <summary>The email conversation between Mats Jerratsch and Nicolas Dorier discusses the use of R values in bipayment channels without HTLCs (Hashed Time-Locked Contracts) in Lightning. They clarify that commitments can't be made before accepting previous ones, and propose a new method for deterministic RValue generation to save off-chain one signature per commitment. Rusty Russell and Nicolas Dorier discuss the idea of one-way deterministic RValue generation and shachain, which avoids generating several million hashes in advance. They also mention Adam Back's contribution to the discussion on the Lightning-dev mailing list in May 2015. The concern is raised about the security implications of disclosing R values when the payment isn't in the current commitment. CJP asks how deriving R values from a tree structure works for larger Lightning networks, and Nicolas Dorier responds with the concept of shachain.</summary>
